<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, A. V. &amp; Smith, A. B. T." box="[199,459,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refId="ref13683" refString="Evans, A. V. &amp; Smith, A. B. T. (2009) Checklist of the New World Melolonthinae, Version 3. Available from: www. museum. unl. edu / research / entomology / SSSA / nwmelos. htm (accessed 14 July 2019)" type="book" year="2009">Evans &amp; Smith (2009)</bibRefCitation>
considered the Nearctic genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1889" box="[831,909,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Pleocomidae" genus="Acoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[831,909,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Acoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saylor" authorityYear="1937" box="[925,1073,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Chaunocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[925,1073,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Chaunocolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1844" box="[1139,1302,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Chnaunanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1139,1302,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Chnaunanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">incertae sedis</emphasis>
, while following the traditional placement of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1856" box="[790,894,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Phobetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,894,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Phobetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Evans" authorityYear="2005" box="[951,1070,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Warwickia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1070,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Warwickia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[1168,1314,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Tanyproctini">Tanyproctini</taxonomicName>
. The tribal placement of all these genera is reconsidered below. During the course of our investigations, all worldwide 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melolonthinae</taxonomicName>
tribes (see 
<tableCitation box="[351,435,261,287]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,622,646]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Extant tribes of Melolonthinae and their distribution (see Bouchard et al. 2011; Löbl &amp; Löbl 2016; Smith &amp; Evans 2018; and the new tribes proposed in this paper)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/6AEA665CF370FFBD2FA8FD90FD38FD5D" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" tableUuid="6AEA665CF370FFBD2FA8FD90FD38FD5D">Table 1</tableCitation>
for a complete list) were studied and we found no compelling morphological characters indicating that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1889" box="[319,397,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Pleocomidae" genus="Acoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,397,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Acoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saylor" authorityYear="1937" box="[411,559,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Chaunocolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[411,559,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Chaunocolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1844" box="[573,736,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Chnaunanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[573,736,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Chnaunanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1856" box="[750,854,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Phobetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[750,854,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Phobetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Evans" authorityYear="2005" box="[899,1018,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Warwickia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[899,1018,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Warwickia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to any of them.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,984,332,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Excluded taxa. Oncerinae new status and Podolasiinae new status</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, A. V." box="[998,1142,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="51 - 60" refId="ref13564" refString="Evans, A. V. (2002) Melolonthinae. In: Arnett, R. H., Thomas, M. C., Skelley, P. E. &amp; Frank, J. H. (Eds.), American Beetles. Vol. 2. Polyphaga: Scarabaeoidea through Curculionoidea. CRC Press, Boca Raton, Florida, pp. 51 - 60." type="book chapter" year="2002">Evans (2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, A. V." box="[1153,1213,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 458" refId="ref13636" refString="Evans, A. V. (2003) A checklist of the New World chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Zootaxa, 211 (1), 1 - 458. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 211.1.1" type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
), Smith (2006), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchard, P. &amp; Bousquet, Y. &amp; Davies, A. E. &amp; Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lawrence, J. F. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. &amp; Newton, A. F. &amp; Reid, C. A. M. &amp; Schmitt, M. &amp; Slipinski, S. A. &amp; Smith, A. B. T." box="[151,405,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 972" refId="ref12994" refString="Bouchard, P., Bousquet, Y., Davies, A. E., Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A., Lawrence, J. F., Lyal, C. H. C., Newton, A. F., Reid, C. A. M., Schmitt, M., Slipinski, S. A. &amp; Smith, A. B. T. (2011) Family-group names in Coleoptera (Insecta). ZooKeys, 88, 1 - 972. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 88.807" type="journal article" year="2011">
Bouchard 
<emphasis box="[268,317,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
all considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1861" box="[577,675,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oncerini">Oncerini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" box="[730,856,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Podolasiini">Podolasiini</taxonomicName>
as tribes within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1252,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melolonthinae</taxonomicName>
. With regards to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,252,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oncerini">Oncerini</taxonomicName>
, we now follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Saylor, L. W." box="[435,592,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="99 - 103" refId="ref15293" refString="Saylor, L. W. (1938) Revision of the subfamily Oncerinae with description of a new genus (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 40, 99 - 103." type="journal article" year="1938">Saylor (1938)</bibRefCitation>
, who considered both 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1856" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1856" box="[841,1108,404,431]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Oncerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,936,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Oncerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte, J. L." box="[942,1108,404,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="225 - 288" refId="ref14527" refString="LeConte, J. L. (1856) Synopsis of the Melolonthidae of the United States. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, Series 2, 3, 225 - 288." type="journal article" year="1856">LeConte, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Saylor, 1938" authorityName="Saylor" authorityYear="1938" box="[1161,1436,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Nefoncerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1161,1289,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Nefoncerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saylor, L. W." box="[1295,1436,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="99 - 103" refId="ref15293" refString="Saylor, L. W. (1938) Revision of the subfamily Oncerinae with description of a new genus (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 40, 99 - 103." type="journal article" year="1938">
Saylor, 
<quantity box="[1380,1436,405,431]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.92252" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="in" value="1938.0">1938</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the subfamily Oncerinae on the basis of the placement of all abdominal spiracles within the pleural membrane. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritcher, P. O." box="[151,314,477,504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="869 - 880" refId="ref14830" refString="Ritcher, P. O. (1969) Spiracles of adult Scarabaeoidea (Coleoptera) and their phylogenetic significance. I. The abdominal spiracles. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 62, 869 - 880. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 62.4.869" type="journal article" year="1969">Ritcher (1969)</bibRefCitation>
confirmed Saylor’s findings for the placement of abdominal spiracles in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1856" box="[1126,1221,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Oncerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1221,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Oncerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but apparently did not examine the more rarely collected 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saylor" authorityYear="1938" box="[577,705,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Nefoncerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[577,705,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Nefoncerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to the placement of their abdominal spiracles, both of these monotypic genera are characterized by having hidden mandibles, labrum fused and coplanar with the clypeus, small and moderately setose lamellate clubs, and abdominal sutures that are distinct or not.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<bibRefCitation author="Howden, H. F." box="[199,376,621,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="223 - 255" refId="ref14253" refString="Howden, H. F. (1997) Podolasiini Howden, new tribe, and a revision of the included genera, Podolasia Harold and Podostena Howden, new genus (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 51, 223 - 255." type="journal article" year="1997">Howden (1997)</bibRefCitation>
erected the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" box="[573,699,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Podolasiini">Podolasiini</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Harold, 1869" authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[747,1017,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podolasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,861,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podolasia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="von Harold, E." box="[868,1017,621,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="976 - 1346" refId="ref13934" refString="von Harold, E. (1869) Scarabaeidae. In: Gemminger, M. &amp; Harold, E. (Eds.), Catalogus Coleopterorum. bucusque descriptorum, synonymicus et systematics, autotribus. Tome IV. Scarabaeidae. E. H. Gummi, Munich, pp. 976 - 1346." type="book chapter" year="1869">Harold, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and his new genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Howden, 1997" authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podostena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1365,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podostena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Howden, H. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="223 - 255" refId="ref14253" refString="Howden, H. F. (1997) Podolasiini Howden, new tribe, and a revision of the included genera, Podolasia Harold and Podostena Howden, new genus (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 51, 223 - 255." type="journal article" year="1997">Howden, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and stated that its position within the 
<taxonomicName box="[714,877,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melolonthinae</taxonomicName>
is “problematical” and “remains debatable since some characters are not typical for the subfamily”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritcher, P. O." box="[716,879,693,720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="869 - 880" refId="ref14830" refString="Ritcher, P. O. (1969) Spiracles of adult Scarabaeoidea (Coleoptera) and their phylogenetic significance. I. The abdominal spiracles. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 62, 869 - 880. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 62.4.869" type="journal article" year="1969">Ritcher (1969)</bibRefCitation>
found 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[957,1071,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podolasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1071,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podolasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to have seven pairs of functional spiracles and a vestigial eighth pair, all located in the pleural membrane. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacroix, M." box="[987,1157,729,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refId="ref14445" refString="Lacroix, M. (2007) Pachydeminae du monde (Coleoptera, Melolonthidae). Genera et catalogue. Collection Hannetons, Paris, 450 pp." type="book" year="2007">Lacroix (2007)</bibRefCitation>
considered the Podolasiinae (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" box="[221,353,765,792]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Podolasiini">Podolasiini</taxonomicName>
), along with the Palaearctic Chasmatopterinae (Chasmatopterini) to be in the Chasmatopteridae without discussion or justification. As mentioned previously, this presumed relationship is untenable given that 
<taxonomicName authority="Dejean, 1821" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[151,488,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Chasmatopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,335,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Chasmatopterus</emphasis>
Dejean, 1821
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[540,654,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podolasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[540,654,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podolasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have very different abdominal spiracle configurations. The lack of any posterior abdominal spiracles in the tergites or sternites, and the small, nearly globose, and densely setose lamellate antennal clubs, combined with the cephalic armature and genital capsule characters found in recently described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[151,265,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podolasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podolasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, A. B. T. &amp; Paulsen, M. J." box="[325,582,945,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="532 - 536" refId="ref15664" refString="Smith, A. B. T. &amp; Paulsen, M. J. (2017) Two new species of Podolasia Harold (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae: Podolasiini) from Coahuila, Mexico. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 71, 532 - 536. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 71.3.532" type="journal article" year="2017">Smith &amp; Paulsen 2017</bibRefCitation>
), and an undescribed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" box="[826,944,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Podostena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,944,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Podostena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (Evans, personal observation) from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,237,981,1007]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Mexico</collectingCountry>
precludes the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1997" box="[543,669,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Podolasiini">Podolasiini</taxonomicName>
within the Melolothinae, thus requiring its elevation to the subfamily rank of Podolasiinae. The phylogenetic position of this new subfamily with relation to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1202,1365,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melolonthinae</taxonomicName>
needs further study and it will likely occupy a branch basal to the phytophagous scarab clade (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, A. B. T. &amp; Hawks, D. C. &amp; Heraty, J. M." box="[1179,1377,1053,1080]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="35 - 46" refId="ref15532" refString="Smith, A. B. T., Hawks, D. C. &amp; Heraty, J. M. (2006) An overview of the classification and evolution of the major scarab beetle clades (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea) based on preliminary molecular analysis. Coleopterists Society Monograph, 5, 35 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X (2006) 60 [35: AOOTCA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[1253,1302,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
